en_508716_0	Brigadier P.J.P Gamage of Sri Lanka Light Infantry assumed duties as the 21st Director in the Directorate of Human Rights and International Humanitarian Law on 18 November.
en_508716_1	The newly-appointed Director left his signature for an official document at the auspicious minute after religious observances and symbolized the acceptance of the new office.
en_508716_2	He succeeded Brigadier A.G.D.N Jayasundara who assumed office as the General Officer Commanding, 23 Division.
en_508716_3	Staff Officers of the Directorate and several Army personnel were present at the location.
